latestPosts.caption:
This one’s for me. 2024 taught me just how heavy life can feel and how strong I’ve had to become to carry it. After losing my dad, fear found its way into places it was never meant to be. Heights I once loved now terrify me. I can’t even sit on a plane peacefully anymore. My mind races: What if it crashes? What if I don’t make it home? Because there are two people waiting for me, counting on me.
Every missed call, every ‘what if,’ every responsibility has weighed on me. I had to grow up too soon, learning to carry pain with a quiet strength, to hold it together even when I felt like falling apart. I learned to let go of people who didn’t serve me not because it was easy, but because my peace is worth it.
But here’s what I’ve realized: I’m still here. Every fear, every sleepless night, every struggle, it didn’t break me. It built me.
As 2025 begins, give yourself a pat on the back. Give yourself credit. You’ve survived battles no one else could see. You’ve carried more than anyone should have to. And you’re still standing. So love yourself, trust yourself, and know this: You’re stronger than you think, and the best is yet to come🫂❤️
